[SINGING
"I'M IN THE MOOD FOR LOVE"]

02:04.400 --> 02:06.960
I'm not too crazy
about that body.

02:07.160 --> 02:10.437
Not too crazy about
that face either, husband.

02:10.639 --> 02:12.597
Oh, boy, after six months,

02:12.800 --> 02:15.156
this is what you've got
to look forward to.

02:15.840 --> 02:17.593
Well, that's too bright,
of course.

02:17.800 --> 02:19.678
I mean, who could look good
in this light?

02:19.880 --> 02:21.553
Right there.

02:23.600 --> 02:25.671
It's too dark.
We'd never find each other.

02:25.880 --> 02:29.635
All right. There, I think.
Good. Good.

02:30.400 --> 02:32.437
Well, she could do worse.

02:32.640 --> 02:33.960
How about a little music, here?

02:34.160 --> 02:35.992
[MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

02:36.200 --> 02:39.637
No, forget it. With my luck,
she'd wanna dance.

02:40.520 --> 02:42.034
Okay.

02:43.160 --> 02:44.640
Whew!

02:46.200 --> 02:48.510
Oh, God, what if I can't?

02:49.680 --> 02:52.434
[SINGING
"I'M IN THE MOOD FOR LOVE"]

03:23.680 --> 03:25.114
Perfect.

03:26.760 --> 03:29.116
Oh, God, what if he can't?

03:29.600 --> 03:32.877
I'll feel like an idiot going out there
dressed like Mae West.

03:33.760 --> 03:36.480
No, I'll go out looking normal.

03:36.680 --> 03:38.512
These feathers will terrify him.

03:38.720 --> 03:41.918
And if I look too magnificent,
he might be overwhelmed.

03:42.120 --> 03:44.351
I'll go out very nonchalant,

03:44.560 --> 03:46.870
like I was expecting nothing.

03:47.440 --> 03:49.432
Maybe I'll carry a book.

03:52.680 --> 03:55.354
So it's got a few feathers.

03:55.560 --> 03:57.552
So what?

03:58.000 --> 04:00.231
Plenty of people go
to sleep like this.

04:01.680 --> 04:03.399
Sure they do.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.913
In Vegas, for $100 a night.

04:26.840 --> 04:28.274
Hi.

04:28.480 --> 04:29.834
Hi.

04:30.320 --> 04:34.678
That new?
Oh, no. I've had it for years.

04:34.880 --> 04:37.236
Oh, well, it's terrific.

04:37.440 --> 04:40.000
It's... It's just polyester.

04:40.200 --> 04:41.873
I mean, it's not silk, or anything.

04:42.080 --> 04:44.720
Actually, I bought it on sale.

04:49.120 --> 04:51.237
You're so beautiful.

04:52.800 --> 04:55.395
Burt.
Mary.

05:08.760 --> 05:11.036
Oh, God. I was a nervous wreck.

05:11.240 --> 05:14.278
I lied. It's brand-new.
I bought it this morning.

05:16.880 --> 05:17.950
[THUMPING]

05:18.160 --> 05:20.595
What was that noise?
That was my heart.

05:21.080 --> 05:22.309
Burt, I heard something.

05:22.520 --> 05:24.796
It, uh... It was the house settling.
Don't worry.

05:25.000 --> 05:28.471
Look. Go look. I'll be nervous.

05:28.920 --> 05:30.559
Don't move.

05:32.256 --> 05:34.176
And don't... Don't... Don't...
Don't fall asleep.

05:34.200 --> 05:37.272
I'll be right back.
Don't even close your eyes.

05:44.600 --> 05:47.035
Danny, Danny, Danny,
what a night you picked to visit.

05:47.240 --> 05:49.921
Hey, come on. Wait a minute.
It's not that I'm not happy to see you.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.640
I am. I love you.
Good to see you, Danny.

05:52.840 --> 05:57.835
Uh, Danny, you see, uh,
your mother and I were upstairs
and we were just gonna...

05:58.040 --> 05:59.360
You know?
You know what I mean?

05:59.560 --> 06:01.552
Hey, it's okay. We got all night.

06:01.760 --> 06:03.991
And maybe we can take
all day tomorrow off.

06:04.200 --> 06:06.032
Hey, Mary, Mary,
look who's here. It's Danny.

06:06.240 --> 06:09.074
Come on, what's the matter with you?
Take that thing off. You're in the house.

06:09.280 --> 06:12.079
Look who's here.
Danny. Ha-ha-ha.

06:13.160 --> 06:14.879
Danny. Mm.

06:18.040 --> 06:21.351
You look so funny. Take that thing off.
He won't. Tell him.

06:21.560 --> 06:22.560
[DOORBELL RINGS]

06:22.720 --> 06:24.359
Wait a minute.
MARY: You put on a little weight, huh?

06:24.560 --> 06:26.279
All right, listen, fella. Forget it.
But listen...

06:26.480 --> 06:28.597
Hey, Aladdin, forget it.
The house is not for sale.

06:28.800 --> 06:31.110
Listen to me...
Hey, Omar, what is it with you guys?

06:31.320 --> 06:33.755
You got yourself a little oil, right?
You get a little crazy.

06:33.960 --> 06:36.156
You and the Japanese are
taking over the whole country.

06:36.360 --> 06:39.280
Next thing you know,
we'll all be eating with chopsticks
and riding camels.

06:39.400 --> 06:40.959
Get out.
Burt. It's me.

06:41.160 --> 06:42.160
Who?
Danny.

06:42.320 --> 06:43.320
No.
Yes.

06:43.480 --> 06:45.711
We already got a Danny.
Burt.

06:45.920 --> 06:47.479
Then who's he?
Hi.

06:47.680 --> 06:49.990
BURT:
Danny. Wait.

06:50.200 --> 06:52.032
Come on, Danny, Danny,
get his mask off.

06:52.240 --> 06:55.119
All right.
Ow! I'll do it.

06:55.320 --> 06:57.240
Come on. What's the idea
of impersonating my son?

06:57.360 --> 06:58.760
I'm not impersonating your son.

06:58.960 --> 07:00.917
You come in here,
you hug me, you kiss Mary.

07:01.120 --> 07:02.554
I didn't hug you.
You hugged me.

07:02.760 --> 07:04.558
What are you doing here,
anyway, huh?

07:04.760 --> 07:07.673
Robbing. What are you doing here,
looking for your tribe?

07:07.880 --> 07:09.560
Come on, come on, come on,
what'd you take?

07:09.600 --> 07:10.920
Nothing.
Come on.

07:11.120 --> 07:12.270
I swear.

07:12.480 --> 07:15.473
All right, I was gonna
take the television set.

07:15.680 --> 07:17.717
But then I realised
that I don't have a car

07:17.920 --> 07:21.550
and I couldn't just walk out of here
and get on the cross-town bus
carrying a 21-inch TV.

07:21.760 --> 07:23.035
So... So I decided to leave.

07:23.240 --> 07:25.072
And then I tripped
on the extension cord.

07:25.280 --> 07:27.556
You keep forgetting to fix that.
It's dangerous.

07:27.760 --> 07:30.798
I know, I could have broken my neck.
As it is, I think I sprained my ankle.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.231
Mary, call the police.
Oh, Burt, he's a kid.

07:33.440 --> 07:34.590
Mary, he's a robber.

07:34.800 --> 07:37.921
Look, mister, this is my first time,
I swear, and my last.
I hate it. I hate it.

07:38.040 --> 07:41.954
I'm a nervous wreck. You can't
believe how dry my mouth is,
you know, from nerves.

07:42.160 --> 07:44.675
And look at this, look at this.
I'm shaking like a leaf.
Look at my hand.

07:44.880 --> 07:45.996
[PHONE RINGS]

07:46.200 --> 07:47.600
You watch him.

07:48.560 --> 07:52.440
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
A person can't get a wink of sleep
around this house.

07:53.400 --> 07:58.031
Oh! And this is nice.
You come in town to
get your camel shoed?

07:59.280 --> 08:02.079
You folks circus people?

08:04.200 --> 08:07.079
Yeah. Yes, it's...

08:09.760 --> 08:11.160
When?

08:12.560 --> 08:17.510
Um... Uh, yes. Yes. Yes.
Yeah, we'll be right there.

08:17.880 --> 08:18.916
What is it?

08:19.760 --> 08:21.592
It was the hospital.

08:22.960 --> 08:25.236
Jodie tried to kill himself.
No. He...

08:25.440 --> 08:28.274
It's okay. It's okay.
He's still alive, but we wanna
get down there right away.

08:28.480 --> 08:29.800
Ma, Ma, he's gonna be okay.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.835
Hey, look, I'm sorry.
If I had a car I'd drive you, but I...

08:34.039 --> 08:36.880
You know, I could have stolen one
last night. A guy left his keys in it.

08:37.080 --> 08:41.039
But I... I... I got a little nervous.

08:42.880 --> 08:44.997
Just locking up for you.

08:46.120 --> 08:48.077
[♪♪♪]

08:52.080 --> 08:55.118
Hi.
Oh, Mr. and Mrs. Campbell.

08:55.320 --> 08:57.755
They said they were bringing Jodie
back up here.

08:57.960 --> 09:01.112
Yeah, that's right.
Hey, he's gonna be all right.

09:01.760 --> 09:04.992
A couple of hours ago, I sneaked
down to intensive care, and I saw him.

09:05.200 --> 09:08.318
I took along a mop
and made believe I was a janitor.

09:08.520 --> 09:11.035
How was he?
He's gonna be fine, really.

09:11.240 --> 09:12.754
Fine? Fine. How fine can he be?

09:12.960 --> 09:16.317
He came here a guy
who wanted to be a girl,
decided he'd rather be a corpse.

09:17.080 --> 09:18.753
I can't stand it.
Quiet.

09:18.960 --> 09:20.189
Well, I have no resistance.

09:20.400 --> 09:23.552
In the elevator alone,
I caught three fatal diseases.

09:23.760 --> 09:25.752
Boys, shh, this is a hospital.

09:25.960 --> 09:29.078
No. I thought it was a discotheque.

09:29.280 --> 09:32.079
Hey, that's nice.
Live entertainment, here.

09:32.280 --> 09:35.000
Oh, get me out of here.
Old sick people depress me.

09:35.200 --> 09:38.716
Hey, hey, hey.
Knock it off.

09:39.480 --> 09:42.598
I'm sorry, Mr. Gerber.
No, that's all right. Listen, he's right.

09:42.800 --> 09:44.234
I am old and sick.

09:44.440 --> 09:47.239
I just thank God
I'm not made of wood.

09:51.080 --> 09:53.117
They're gonna bring him right up.

09:53.320 --> 09:58.520
Oh, boy. This is some treat.
A hostile doll, and now an Arab.

09:59.320 --> 10:01.198
I don't know who I love more, here.

10:01.400 --> 10:02.993
Hey, how you doing?
Fine. Listen.

10:03.200 --> 10:06.637
I think before you get too friendly,
you should know I'm Jewish.

10:06.840 --> 10:08.035
Mr. Gerber, it's me.

10:10.600 --> 10:13.911
Yes, I know you. Who are you?

10:14.120 --> 10:15.270
I'm Danny.

10:15.480 --> 10:17.119
That's not an Arab name.

10:17.320 --> 10:18.640
I'm Jodie's brother, Danny.

10:18.840 --> 10:21.912
Oh! That's it. Last time,
you were a girl nurse.

10:22.120 --> 10:23.839
That's right.

10:24.600 --> 10:28.037
Hey, it must take you a while
to get dressed in the morning.

10:28.480 --> 10:29.480
BURT:
Ah!

10:29.680 --> 10:30.801
Hi, Danny.
DANNY: Hey, Jodie.

10:30.960 --> 10:32.394
Hi, Burt. Hi, Chuck.

10:32.600 --> 10:35.195
Well, if at first
you don't succeed...

10:36.320 --> 10:37.549
How do you feel?

10:37.760 --> 10:41.231
All right.
I'm just a little tired, that's all.

10:41.440 --> 10:44.433
Barney, that story you told me
really made me wanna live.

10:44.640 --> 10:46.597
But I was just too sleepy
to tell you.

10:46.800 --> 10:47.800
BURT:
Hey, hey, hey.

10:48.000 --> 10:51.201
Hey, you sure you're okay?
I mean, they said you could
come home in a couple days.

10:51.400 --> 10:53.596
I mean, do we have to start
throwing out aspirins,
hiding razor blades, what?

10:53.800 --> 10:56.474
Burt, Burt, please.
That's not something
I'm ever gonna do again.

10:56.680 --> 10:59.036
Yeah, please. I hope not.

10:59.240 --> 11:01.675
And I've also decided not to
have the sex-change operation.

11:02.000 --> 11:03.559
DANNY:
Oh!

11:03.760 --> 11:07.470
Wonderful. You lose a daughter,
you gain a suicidal sissy.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.795
Hey, shut him up, will you?
Hey, go pitch a tent.

11:11.136 --> 11:13.256
CHUCK [IN NORMAL VOICE]:
We're leaving. We're leaving.

11:13.280 --> 11:14.350
Good, I hate it here.

11:14.560 --> 11:17.519
With all these germs,
God knows what I caught.

11:17.720 --> 11:20.519
If there's a God, maybe termites.

11:22.240 --> 11:24.516
Jodie, I gotta take off.
I'll see you soon, all right?

11:24.720 --> 11:27.189
All right, I'm coming down with you.
I'll see you at home, all right?

11:27.400 --> 11:29.517
JODIE: Okay.
Mary, we'll be downstairs.

11:29.720 --> 11:31.552
Mr. Gerber.
Mr. Campbell.

11:31.760 --> 11:33.114
I'm sorry, Ma.

11:33.320 --> 11:35.437
It's okay, as long as
you're all right.

11:35.640 --> 11:37.359
It was a stupid thing to do.

11:37.560 --> 11:38.789
You were upset.

11:39.280 --> 11:41.351
That's no reason to take 45 pills.

11:41.560 --> 11:42.914
Forty-five?

11:43.120 --> 11:44.918
How did you do that?

11:45.120 --> 11:47.316
You've never been able
to swallow pills.

11:47.520 --> 11:50.752
You still break aspirin in half
because they're too big.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.758
It was just a stupid thing to do.

11:52.960 --> 11:55.395
Well, there's something
I always say.

11:55.600 --> 11:59.799
In your life, you're entitled
to one really stupid thing.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.116
Right?

12:01.320 --> 12:03.277
I say five.

12:04.520 --> 12:06.637
Five stupid things.

12:06.840 --> 12:11.790
Oh. Well, I guess I say one
because I once did
a really, really stupid thing.

12:12.000 --> 12:13.673
What?
Oh, I can't tell you.

12:13.880 --> 12:14.880
Oh, come on, Ma.

12:15.080 --> 12:17.675
No. It was the stupidest thing
I've ever done.

12:17.880 --> 12:19.155
[CHUCKLING]

12:19.360 --> 12:22.478
I can't tell you. No.

12:22.680 --> 12:25.673
No, I can't. I'll tell you
about the time I...

12:25.880 --> 12:27.758
[LAUGHING]

12:27.960 --> 12:29.838
I can't tell you that either.

12:30.520 --> 12:32.352
Um... Okay, I got it.

12:32.560 --> 12:34.916
I'll tell you about when I once, uh...

12:35.600 --> 12:36.795
I once...

12:37.000 --> 12:38.639
[LAUGHING]

12:41.240 --> 12:45.154
Oh, God, I can't tell you that.
That's the most awful.

12:46.640 --> 12:48.393
Okay, I got it.

12:52.720 --> 12:55.599
That's worse than all the others.

12:55.800 --> 12:58.156
So that's four stupid things.

12:58.480 --> 12:59.480
Is it?
Yeah.

12:59.680 --> 13:02.479
Four stupid things that are
so stupid you can't tell us.

13:03.160 --> 13:04.753
Well, I guess you're right.

13:04.960 --> 13:07.555
We're entitled to five stupid things.

13:07.760 --> 13:11.640
I told you, five. What do you think,
I made that up? That's a statistic.

13:12.920 --> 13:15.913
So I guess you've got four more.

13:17.160 --> 13:18.640
But please,

13:19.280 --> 13:21.078
no more like this one.

13:21.280 --> 13:22.634
Okay, I promise.

13:22.840 --> 13:25.435
I'm stupid, but I'm not that stupid.

13:25.880 --> 13:27.394
Okay.

13:27.880 --> 13:29.519
Go to sleep.

13:32.640 --> 13:34.199
I'll see you tomorrow.

13:34.400 --> 13:35.400
Okay.

13:36.720 --> 13:38.359
Good night, Mr. Gerber.

13:38.560 --> 13:41.359
Good night.
Good night, Mrs. Campbell.

13:41.840 --> 13:44.799
Well, she's...
She's all right, that lady.

13:45.120 --> 13:46.315
Yep.

13:46.720 --> 13:51.431
Her husband, uh...
He's a little nervous,
but he means well.

13:51.640 --> 13:56.032
And your brother is a nice guy.
I just worry about him
tripping over his robe.

13:56.760 --> 13:59.355
But that wooden fellow...

14:00.080 --> 14:01.560
He's not related.

14:01.760 --> 14:04.195
Well, I didn't think he was.
I mean, he's wood.

14:05.640 --> 14:07.154
I don't know.

14:07.360 --> 14:10.319
I don't know what the world
is coming to anymore

14:10.520 --> 14:13.911
when a gay man, who was thinking
of becoming a woman

14:14.120 --> 14:16.271
then decides on suicide,

14:16.480 --> 14:20.076
turns out to be the most normal
member of the family.

14:20.920 --> 14:22.877
[♪♪♪]

14:26.040 --> 14:27.872
[♪♪♪]

14:35.720 --> 14:37.871
Oh, uh, hi, babe. What's up?

14:38.080 --> 14:40.197
I should ask you that.

14:40.400 --> 14:42.039
What are you talking about, Corinne?

14:42.240 --> 14:44.277
I'm talking about walking
into the pro shop

14:44.480 --> 14:47.040
and finding you
licking some woman's ear.

14:47.240 --> 14:49.038
What are you, crazy?
That was Mrs. Carr.

14:49.240 --> 14:51.277
I was, uh, giving her some pointers
for the tournament tomorrow.

14:51.480 --> 14:53.756
I had to whisper,
in case her opponent walked in.

14:53.960 --> 14:56.873
Oh, really? Is that a fact?
And two hours ago,

14:57.080 --> 14:59.834
when you said you had a lesson
on Court 3, where were you?

15:00.040 --> 15:02.236
I said Court 5.
You weren't on Court 5.

15:02.440 --> 15:04.750
Did I say 5? It wasn't 5. It was 8.

15:04.960 --> 15:08.158
Look, I saw the girl you gave
a lesson to in the locker room.

15:08.360 --> 15:11.114
An hour's lesson in this heat,
and she wasn't sweating.

15:11.320 --> 15:12.834
She was smiling.

15:13.280 --> 15:15.192
I know. It's incredible.

15:15.400 --> 15:19.280
The girl doesn't sweat.
Has never perspired in her life.

15:19.480 --> 15:21.520
She was telling me about it.
It's a medical problem.

15:21.600 --> 15:23.910
Very dangerous, actually,
because when she can't sweat,

15:24.120 --> 15:27.955
she can't rid her body of toxins and
can poison herself to death. Poor thing.

15:28.840 --> 15:32.629
Peter, I found hairpins in our bed.
I don't use hairpins.

15:32.840 --> 15:35.196
I do.
You use hairpins?

15:35.400 --> 15:37.551
Sure, when I run out of paper clips.

15:37.760 --> 15:39.513
I found a pink headband.

15:39.720 --> 15:41.154
Mine.
Pink.

15:41.360 --> 15:43.397
Used to be red. Faded.

15:43.600 --> 15:46.752
Look, Peter, I know what you were,
but if we're gonna live together,

15:46.960 --> 15:50.749
you're gonna have to stop
fooling around with other women,
or I'll leave.

15:50.960 --> 15:53.520
Honey, I'm not fooling around.

15:53.720 --> 15:56.792
I'm a teacher.
I gotta get to know my students.

15:57.000 --> 15:59.151
To teach them the inner game.
That's all it is.

16:00.280 --> 16:04.160
Okay. Okay. But I've given up
a lot for you, Peter.

16:04.360 --> 16:06.670
I've given up my home
and my family,

16:06.880 --> 16:08.951
someone who's very important
to me.

16:09.440 --> 16:13.639
So if you're lying to me
and I catch you,

16:13.840 --> 16:16.150
I swear, Peter, I'll kill you.

16:16.360 --> 16:20.195
Oh, Corinne, Corinne, Corinne.

16:20.400 --> 16:22.119
[MOUTHING]

16:25.880 --> 16:27.837
[♪♪♪]

16:36.080 --> 16:37.560
Hi, Jess.

16:37.760 --> 16:42.357
I hope you weren't worried
when I didn't come home last night.
I worked so late, I stayed in town.

16:42.680 --> 16:46.560
Chester, I, uh, saw you yesterday.

16:46.760 --> 16:49.116
Well, Jessica,
you see me every day.

16:49.320 --> 16:53.155
I saw you eating lunch
and kissing Claire.

16:55.280 --> 16:57.840
Eating lunch and kissing Claire?

16:58.040 --> 17:01.033
I remember the eating.
I had the roast beef.

17:01.240 --> 17:05.871
It was so tough, I had to send it back.
But I, uh, don't remember the kissing.

17:06.359 --> 17:07.999
Wait. Yes, of course.

17:08.200 --> 17:11.000
It was Claire's birthday
and she gave me a kiss
for taking her to lunch.

17:11.079 --> 17:12.400
That's what it was.
No, Chester.

17:12.599 --> 17:14.796
You were kissing her on the neck.

17:15.000 --> 17:18.789
I wasn't kissing her on the neck,
Jessica. I was smelling her neck.

17:19.240 --> 17:22.074
She wanted me to smell the perfume
she'd gotten as a present.

17:22.280 --> 17:23.280
Please, Chester.

17:23.440 --> 17:26.353
You had your face burrowed
so deep in her neck for so long,

17:26.560 --> 17:30.315
I was surprised
you weren't asphyxiated.

17:31.760 --> 17:34.958
That was to look
at the rash, Jessica.

17:36.000 --> 17:39.835
The perfume she wanted me to smell
gave her a rash that
she wanted me to look at.

17:40.040 --> 17:42.635
In fact, I sent her straight
to the dermatologist.

17:42.840 --> 17:44.718
You know, Chester,
in all these years,

17:44.920 --> 17:48.072
I've never believed the stories
that people told about you.

17:48.280 --> 17:51.159
But now I...
Stories. Oh, Jessica.

17:51.360 --> 17:53.636
Do you know why people
make up stories like that?

17:53.840 --> 17:55.559
It's because they're jealous.

17:55.760 --> 17:59.834
You see, they have so little
themselves that they can't
stand to see us happy. So...

18:00.040 --> 18:02.680
Oh, enough. Chester, please.

18:02.880 --> 18:06.032
Do you know how
that makes me feel, Chester?

18:06.240 --> 18:07.913
Do you know?

18:08.240 --> 18:11.836
To realise that my husband
has been carrying on with every...

18:12.040 --> 18:16.239
Oh, fine, Jessica.
Go ahead. Believe filth.

18:16.440 --> 18:19.877
How would you feel, Chester,
if you found out I had had an affair?

18:20.080 --> 18:21.275
You?

18:21.480 --> 18:22.880
[LAUGHING]

18:25.400 --> 18:26.993
What is so funny?

18:27.200 --> 18:30.591
Oh, well, I'm sorry, Jessica,
but I mean, I just don't think of you

18:30.800 --> 18:33.634
as someone who has an affair,
that's all.

18:33.840 --> 18:36.594
You and Julie Andrews.

18:37.880 --> 18:39.872
Well, Chester, I had one.

18:40.080 --> 18:42.117
Really? With whom?

18:42.320 --> 18:46.519
That is not important, Chester.
I mean, really, the name is
not important.

18:46.720 --> 18:51.431
Jessica, if you think that by telling me
about an affair you've never had

18:51.640 --> 18:54.474
you're going to get me to admit
to affairs I've never had,

18:54.680 --> 18:55.955
you're crazy.

18:56.520 --> 18:57.920
It's true, Chester.

18:58.120 --> 19:01.352
Oh, Jessica, you are funny.
Ha-ha-ha!

19:01.680 --> 19:03.319
I'm not funny, Chester.

19:03.520 --> 19:05.989
If there is one thing
I am not right now, it's funny.

19:06.200 --> 19:08.431
So will you please stop laughing?

19:10.920 --> 19:13.071
You were never here, Chester.

19:13.280 --> 19:16.751
And I mean, when you were here,
somehow, you weren't really here.

19:16.960 --> 19:18.917
Just like Fluffy.

19:21.240 --> 19:22.469
What?

19:22.680 --> 19:25.400
Well, you remember Fluffy,
the cat we had.

19:25.600 --> 19:28.354
I mean, you know, she would eat
and she would wash herself

19:28.560 --> 19:30.995
and then she'd just lay around,
you know?

19:31.200 --> 19:33.635
And I don't believe once,
in all those years,

19:33.840 --> 19:35.957
that she ever really looked
at any of us.

19:36.160 --> 19:37.753
I mean, of course,
it was hard to tell.

19:37.960 --> 19:40.475
With all that hair, you couldn't see
if her eyes were open.

19:40.680 --> 19:44.071
Which was, of course,
why we called her Fluffy.

19:45.840 --> 19:49.151
I mean, Chester,
that's why I had an affair.

19:54.120 --> 19:56.635
Because of Fluffy?

20:00.240 --> 20:03.517
Chester, it was short.

20:04.040 --> 20:08.239
It wasn't very spectacular.
And it is over now,

20:08.440 --> 20:10.671
but, you know, for a little while,

20:10.880 --> 20:13.076
minutes maybe,

20:13.280 --> 20:15.749
somebody was really there.

20:16.720 --> 20:18.279
You had an affair?

20:20.200 --> 20:23.272
You mean,
you slept with another man?

20:23.480 --> 20:27.474
Well, I mean, Chester,
that's usually what an affair is.

20:28.320 --> 20:30.073
How could you?

20:30.520 --> 20:32.989
How could you do that to me?

20:34.080 --> 20:35.960
How many people know
about this affair, Jessica?

20:36.000 --> 20:38.037
How many people have you
bragged to about it?

20:38.240 --> 20:39.799
I never bragged about it, Chester.

20:40.000 --> 20:43.880
I mean, that isn't something
I exactly felt like bragging about.

20:44.080 --> 20:45.514
I trusted you, Jessica.

20:45.720 --> 20:48.997
All these years, I trusted you.

20:49.840 --> 20:54.278
And you went out and had a cheap,
dirty, sordid little affair.

20:55.520 --> 20:57.796
Well, Chester,
I don't think of it that way.

20:58.000 --> 21:02.233
I mean I did think of it that way
for a while,

21:02.440 --> 21:03.874
but I don't anymore.

21:04.080 --> 21:06.720
I mean, I prefer to think of it as

21:07.240 --> 21:09.152
something that happened.

21:09.360 --> 21:11.079
Something that happened?

21:11.280 --> 21:14.398
Chester, what I did was wrong,

21:14.600 --> 21:17.638
and I am not trying to minimise it
by saying this,

21:17.840 --> 21:20.719
but I mean, Chester,
what I did for a few weeks,

21:20.920 --> 21:23.435
you made into a career.

21:29.280 --> 21:31.078
What are you talking about?

21:31.280 --> 21:34.273
Chester, surely you are not
going to go on denying...

21:34.480 --> 21:37.359
I am.
You have never been unfaithful?

21:37.560 --> 21:40.553
That's right. Never. I never have,
and I never would. Not once, not ever.

21:40.760 --> 21:44.674
Because I, Jessica, believe
in the sanctity of our marriage.

21:45.840 --> 21:47.194
Chester?
What?

21:47.400 --> 21:49.631
Blow it out your ears.

21:53.160 --> 21:54.160
Jessica.

21:54.360 --> 21:58.036
You know what's really funny,
Chester?

21:58.240 --> 22:00.596
I mean, this is the first time
in all these years

22:00.800 --> 22:04.157
we've ever talked about anything
that really matters.

22:04.360 --> 22:06.591
And you're not even
really talking, Chester.

22:06.800 --> 22:11.079
I mean, please, let's be honest
with each other, for God's sake.

22:11.280 --> 22:14.193
I mean, that's all we've got left to be.

22:14.400 --> 22:16.631
Well, I have been honest, Jessica.

22:22.880 --> 22:24.314
All right, Chester.

22:28.360 --> 22:29.555
Where you going?
I don't know.

22:29.760 --> 22:31.479
What do you mean, you don't know?
Just what I said.

22:31.680 --> 22:34.752
Jessica. You can't just leave.

22:36.880 --> 22:39.440
Just watch, Chester.

